{"lemma":"كَرْمُ","slug":"كَرْمُ","root":"ك.ر.م","root_slug":"ك-ر-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-ر-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كَرْمُ","root":"كرم","pos":"V","occurrence_count":2},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":10},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n42992","n42998"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%B1%D9%92%D9%85%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become noble"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become generous"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be or become precious"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to call (someone) noble"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to honor, to venerate"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to exalt"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of كَرُمَ (karuma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nobleness, kindness"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"generosity","examples":[{"text":"لمدينة عرتا لها ذاكرة في قلوب الصوماليين، حيث إحتضنت نقبة كبيرة من المجتمع الصومالي، وأنها أصبحت رمزا للكرم والسخاء.","english":"The town of ʿartā is of avid memory with the Somalis in that it embraced a large swathe of Somali society and became a symbol of openhandedness and generosity."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"vineyard, vines, orchard","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Compare Ugaritic 𐎋𐎗𐎎 (krm, “vineyard”), Aramaic כַּרְמָא (karmā, “vineyard”), Hebrew כֶּרֶם (kérem, “vineyard”), Akkadian 𒃾 (karānum, “wine, vine, grapes”), and the possible etymon Egyptian kꜣm. Due to the small difference in the third consonant of the Akkadian form, the Dictionnaire du faisceau dialectal arabe andalou suggests a borrowing from a language of Anatolia, the same suspicion as for Proto-West Semitic *wayn- (“grape”), and additionally speculates that the homonymic root related to nobleness derived from the name of the vine plant."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n42992","headword_ar":"كَرُمَ","root":"krm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karamN","text_ar":"كَرَمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It"},{"kind":"text","text":"(a thing)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, highly esteemed"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"prized"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"valued; excellent, precious, valuable,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rare:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) followed by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ealayohi","text_ar":"عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":": see 1 in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fjE","text_ar":"فجع"},{"kind":"text","text":". ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karumato","text_ar":"كَرُمَتْ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aroDuhu","text_ar":"اَرْضُهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His land yielded increase of its seed-produce,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and its soil became good,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being manured;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(ISh, K;) [or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it was,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"became, generous,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"good;"},{"kind":"text","text":"i. e.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"productive,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"fertile"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. ―         -b3-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"karumotu Ealayohi","text_ar":"كَرُمْتُ عَلَيْهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K, art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Ez","text_ar":"عز"},{"kind":"text","text":",)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I exceeded him in generosity,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"noblenes